cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with stereo reconstruction and semantic segmentation of satellite images. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of satellite images for 3D mapping suggests a robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of semantic segmentation suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of ground truth labels suggests a graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
